ccfe (2.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Runtime configuration reload: a "reload" action/key re-reads the config and
    re-applies colours, key bindings, behaviour toggles and variables without a
    restart (mouse/layout/restricted still need one).
  * Colour-theme switching from the menu: "Select colour theme" lists the
    installed themes, persists the choice (a `theme = NAME` global) and applies
    it at once; smit-panel and console themes are advertised alongside smit.
  * Key maps: a `keymap { }` config section and a runtime "Select key map"
    switcher with shipped presets (classic, safe, nano, mc). Bindings now accept
    Meta/Alt (M-x) and Ctrl (^X) chords and plain keys, primary plus alternates,
    not only the function keys; a small ESC-disambiguating input layer (ESCDELAY)
    drives the Meta chords. The footer labels follow the function, not the key.
  * Menu/form search: a "search" action/key scans every object on the path
    (titles, top/bottom text, item descriptions, field labels) and jumps to a
    match.
  * Notifications: a `notify_file` global is polled and shown as a banner on
    menu entry (each distinct write once).
  * Ownership management: ccfe-build gains chown / list-users / list-groups /
    list-objects and a builder form, to change the owner of your own objects.
  * Run CCFE at login: a new `-R`/`--restricted` flag forces the kiosk sandbox
    for a run, and the ccfe-login helper (+ a "Login / shell setup" config menu)
    hooks a shell profile to start CCFE on an interactive login/SSH, system-wide
    or per-user, optionally as a locked kiosk.
  * No change to the menu/form/config file formats or to default behaviour. Full
    detail is in the git history.

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Fri, 12 Jun 2026 20:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.3.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix a menu rendering bug: a long top{} description no longer collides with
    the menu. The top-message area is now sized to the wrapped message height
    (word-wrapped to the screen width) and the menu is drawn below it, instead
    of the menu overdrawing the last line(s) of the description. The mouse
    click-to-item mapping was updated to match the dynamic top area.

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Config variables: a new `variables {}` config section defines $NAME values
    (cross-referencing each other) that are substituted into menu/form actions
    and field list_cmds -- to cut duplication across objects. See ccfe.conf(5).
  * Guided configuration wizard (`ccfe config`): forms that walk through screen
    layout, behaviour toggles, shell/restricted mode and defining a variable,
    writing the user's personal ccfe.conf via ccfe-build.
  * Builder: edit an existing menu item's description (`ccfe builder`).
  * A docker-compose "remembered commands" shell (a curated admin/debug menu).
  * Output browser fills its whole pane with the panel background under a theme
    (no more "themed text, black gaps"); a missing `exec:` command now shows a
    clear pop-up instead of an opaque exit; the bundled sysmon demo gained
    core-tool tasks (df/du/ps/ss/free/uptime/who) that need no sysstat package.
  * Internal: the oversized ccfe.pl subs (do_form, load_config, run_browse,
    do_menu, do_list, load_form) were broken up behind a strengthened pty test
    net, and ccfe.pl is now perltidy-clean and under the CI lint gate.
  * No change to the menu/form/config file formats or to normal interactive
    behaviour. Full detail is in the git history.

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Completes the M7 de-globalisation: the .menu/.form/.conf parsers, the
    action-string parser and the form value-column/page geometry are now pure,
    unit-tested CCFE::* modules, and ccfe.pl's package globals and `local`
    dynamic scope are replaced by lexicals and an explicit $ctx run-state
    object. ccfe.pl now runs under `use v5.36` (strict + warnings); this raises
    the requirement to Perl >= 5.36 (already declared).
  * While the screen is in curses mode, Perl warnings are routed to the log
    instead of being printed over the display, so a stray warning on an edge
    path can no longer corrupt the TUI.
  * Non-functional close-out audit (ROADMAP M8, see M8-AUDIT.md): assorted
    small correctness fixes (numeric comparisons, dead code, an eval-string
    replaced by sprintf) and documentation/version-consistency fixes. Restricted
    mode's true scope is now documented honestly in the README (it is a
    guardrail, not a hardened security boundary).
  * No change to the menu/form/config file formats or to normal interactive
    behaviour.

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Wed, 11 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Internal modularisation (ROADMAP M7); no functional change. The menu, form
    and config file parsers, the action-string parser and the form value-column
    /page geometry are extracted into pure, terminal-free CCFE::* modules under
    lib/perl5, each unit-tested directly (CCFE::MenuFile, CCFE::FormFile,
    CCFE::Config, CCFE::Action, CCFE::Layout). The two duplicated copies of the
    action parse and of the resize geometry are now single shared
    implementations, so they can no longer drift apart.
  * Test suite grown to 302 tests; behaviour verified unchanged by the existing
    on-screen resize/layout/multipage and colour integration tests.

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Wed, 11 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Terminal-resize reflow: menus and forms re-paginate, re-right-align and
    re-wrap to the new size; resizing no longer crashes or leaves values
    off-screen; pop-up list / output browser re-centre and rebuild on resize.
  * Forms lay out by display column, not byte count, so accented / wide-char
    labels position correctly (optional libtext-charwidth-perl).
  * Over-long labels wrap onto their own line(s) with the value below, rather
    than being pushed off-screen.
  * Full foreground/background colour palette: color_pair('fg','bg') in any
    *_attr value gives a panelled SMIT look applied across menus, forms and the
    output browser; new ccfe.conf.smit-panel theme.
  * Field flag markers and the leader dots adopt the theme colour; show_dots
    can switch the dot run off.
  * F8 / redraw and resize now force a full repaint; uncaught errors restore
    the terminal with a clean message.
  * New `ccfe --dump NAME` (-D) prints a menu/form as JSON for scripting.
  * Opt-in mouse (`mouse = YES`): click a menu item to select, double-click to
    activate.
  * New `ccfe --plugins` (-P) lists installed plugin manifests; plugins may
    ship a `<name>.plugin` file (sample sysmon plugin does).

 -- CCFE maintainers <ccfedevel@gmail.com>  Wed, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

ccfe (2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CCFE 2.0.
  * Reorganised install layout: menus/forms under share/ccfe/objects, themes
    under share/ccfe/themes; per-user files follow the XDG base directories.
  * Paths resolved at runtime from the program location (relocatable; no
    install-time templating).
  * Restricted mode and command-execution hardening.
  * Optional colour, including menu/header/control-key theming and the classic
    and colour SMIT themes.
  * "ccfe -k NAME" parse-check linter.

